# Test Case Documentation Standards

## Test Case Documentation Structure

All test cases must be documented following the specified directory structure and format, mirroring the feature file organization.

### Documentation Directory Structure
```
TestCaseDocumentation/
├── {ModuleName}/
│   ├── {EndpointName}_ReadMe.md
│   ├── {EndpointName2}_ReadMe.md
│   └── {EndpointName3}_ReadMe.md
├── {ModuleName2}/
│   ├── {EndpointName}_ReadMe.md
│   └── {EndpointName2}_ReadMe.md
└── README.md (Master index)
```

### Documentation File Locations
- **Master Index**: `TestCaseDocumentation/README.md`
- **Module Documentation**: `TestCaseDocumentation/{ModuleName}/README.md`
- **Endpoint Documentation**: `TestCaseDocumentation/{ModuleName}/{EndpointName}_ReadMe.md`

### Directory Structure Examples
```
TestCaseDocumentation/
├── Zones/
│   ├── zones_add_ReadMe.md
│   ├── zones_list_ReadMe.md
│   └── zones_update_ReadMe.md
├── Users/
│   ├── users_create_ReadMe.md
│   ├── users_login_ReadMe.md
│   └── users_profile_ReadMe.md
├── Orders/
│   ├── orders_create_ReadMe.md
│   ├── orders_list_ReadMe.md
│   └── orders_update_ReadMe.md
└── README.md
```

